description:
Give the unforgettable flavor combination of Hershey’s Golden Almond Chocolate Bars: crunchy roasted California almonds nestled in rich, delicious Hershey’s Milk Chocolate. This golden gift box contains 5 big bars, and each 2.8-ounce bar is individually wrapped in gold foil. Altogether, it’s 14 ounces of pure delight. The ideal gift for chocolate aficionados.

More Precious than Gold -- These gold-foiled Hershey’s Golden Almond Chocolate Bars are perfect for planning a couple’s 50th wedding anniversary party, or showing your loved one you’re still sweet on them after all these years.

For Party Favors that Shine -- Go for party-planning gold by customizing printable labels and applying one to each bar of fine milk chocolate with roasted almonds. Since the candy bars are already wrapped in gold foil, it’s a deliciously easy way to make party favors that really shine!

Take Home a Treasured Treat -- Gold is precious and so are these bars!

The Hershey’s Golden Almond Chocolate Bar Gift Box is a treasure of a treat for your special occasions. Distinguish the moment with these distinctively unique Hershey’s Chocolate Bars. The Hershey Legacy -- The story of Hershey’s Chocolate begins with Milton S. Hershey. Trained as a confectioner and owner of a successful caramel factory, Hershey became fascinated with chocolate-making at the 1893 World’s Columbian Exposition. Hershey founded the Hershey Chocolate Company in 1894, and built what would become the world's largest chocolate factory in 1903. He then created the model industrial town of Hershey, Pennsylvania, where workers enjoyed comfortable homes, inexpensive public transport, and quality public schools. In 1909, Hershey and his wife, Catherine, established a school for orphan boys. Hershey eventually endowed the bulk of his wealth to this school, including his ownership of the Hershey Chocolate Company. For more than a century, Milton Hershey School has enriched the lives of countless children in need. The town of Hershey, Pennsylvania has provided employment, recreation, and culture. And The Hershey Company has brought smiles to people around the world.
